    stem: "A 24-year-old woman presents with irregular periods (every 45–90 days) since menarche, facial acne, and excess facial hair for 3 years. Her BMI is 28 kg/m². Examination reveals mild hirsutism (Ferriman-Gallwey score 11/36). Investigations show: LH 12 IU/L, FSH 4 IU/L, testosterone 2.9 nmol/L (reference <2.5 nmol/L), SHBG 22 nmol/L (low), prolactin normal, TSH normal, 17-OHP 4 nmol/L (normal <6 nmol/L). Pelvic ultrasound shows 14 follicles per ovary, each <10mm, with increased ovarian volume. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
