    stem: "A 72-year-old man with known atrial fibrillation is referred by his cardiologist. He is on warfarin, digoxin, and amiodarone (started 8 months ago). He presents with weight loss of 5 kg, heat intolerance, palpitations, and tremor. TSH is <0.01 mU/L, free T4 is 42 pmol/L, and free T3 is 8.9 pmol/L. He has no goitre and thyroid antibodies are negative. Radioactive iodine uptake scan shows diffusely low uptake (<1%) throughout the thyroid. What type of amiodarone-induced thyrotoxicosis does he most likely have?",
