    stem: "A 38-year-old woman presents to the emergency department with a 6-hour history of severe abdominal pain, vomiting, and confusion. She was recently diagnosed with primary adrenal insufficiency 3 weeks ago and commenced on hydrocortisone and fludrocortisone. She has had a gastroenteritis illness for 2 days and was unable to keep her medications down. On examination: BP 80/50 mmHg, HR 122 bpm, temperature 38.2°C. Sodium is 128 mmol/L, potassium 5.8 mmol/L, glucose 2.8 mmol/L. What is the most important immediate treatment?",
