    stem: `A 29-year-old woman presents to your GP clinic with complaints of mood swings, palpitation, and fine tremors for the past few weeks. Laboratory tests are ordered, and the results are remarkable for a decreased TSH level and normal T3 and T4. Which one of the following is most likely to be the cause of this presentation?`,
