    topic: "Endocrinology",
    subtopic: "Osteoporosis management with teriparatide",
    stem: `Three months ago, you started Mary, aged 73, on risedronate 35mg weekly after she was diagnosed with osteoporosis, confirmed with bone mineral density (BMD). Her presenting symptom at that time was back pain. Examination revealed a height decrease, mild kyphosis, and tenderness over thoracic vertebrae. Despite being on risedronate, her symptoms persisted, and she also developed pain over new areas of her thoracic vertebrae. A new X-ray established new osteoporotic fractures. Which of the following would be the most appropriate management option for her?`,
